  "updateinfo_id": "ALSA-2026:41892",
  "description": "The libtiff packages contain a library of functions for manipulating Tagged Image File Format (TIFF) files.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * libtiff: TIFFRasterScanlineSize64 produce too-big size and could cause OOM (CVE-2023-52355)\n  * libtiff: libtiff: Heap-based buffer overflow via crafted PixarLog-compressed TIFF image (CVE-2026-12912)\n\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):  \n\n  * Reintroduce the `tiffcp -i` option (JIRA:AlmaLinux-185328)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
  "fromstr": "packager@almalinux.org",
